ad of global markets for the Americas. SocGen is also expanding its rates b=
usiness for Latin America with new hires in New York.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe end of the zero-rates regime crea=
tes more opportunities for our platform,=E2=80=9D New York-based Farah said=
 in an interview. =E2=80=9CInstitutional clients like private equity and in=
surers are actively hedging on the rates side. It=E2=80=99s not temporary a=
nd it=E2=80=99s part of our rates strategy in the US.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">International banks including=C2=A0Barclays Pl=
c=C2=A0and=C2=A0Nomura Holdings Inc.=C2=A0are also making moves to bolster =
trading operations. In US rates, the biggest banks are set to make $19.2 bi=
llion in revenue this year, according to predictions from Vali Analytics.</=
p>
</blockquote>
