ad of partnerships, who recruited Brady and=C2=A0B=C3=BCndchen to endorse F=
TX in exchange for almost $50 million of FTX stock:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A former college football player, Mr. Nader wa=
s in charge of recruiting Mr. Brady and other stars. In June 2021, Mr. Brad=
y and Ms. B=C3=BCndchen agreed to a deal with Mr. Bankman-Fried, praising t=
he =E2=80=9Crevolutionary FTX team.=E2=80=9D Mr. Brady seemed genuinely int=
erested in crypto, Mr. Nader said, and occasionally had conversations with =
Mr. Bankman-Fried.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CImagine a tiger and a lion talking,=
=E2=80=9D Mr. Nader said. =E2=80=9CThey=E2=80=99re slightly different, they=
 do different things, but they=E2=80=99re really formidable in their own ar=
enas.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Imagine a tiger and a lion talking. Imagine To=
m Brady and Sam Bankman-Fried talking. About crypto. Imagine Tom Brady and =
Sam Bankman-Fried talking about football. Imagine them talking about pandem=
ic preparedness. Nutritional supplements. AI alignment.=C2=A0<em>Succession=
</em>. Imagine a weekly podcast in which Tom Brady and Sam Bankman-Fried di=
scuss the week=E2=80=99s news and pop culture. I feel like if I were in cha=
rge of FTX=E2=80=99s bankruptcy I would be working to develop that podcast =
and sell it to Spotify. Bankman-Fried is facing a whole lot of prison, and =
Brady has been sued by disgruntled FTX customers, and I think both of them =
could improve their legal position significantly if FTX were just able to p=
ay back its customers, and I feel like that podcast could bring in, what,=
=C2=A0$2 billion?<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgr=
ound-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0No, no, probably not, but=C2=A0<em>I=C2=A0</em>would listen to it=
, and I am sad I can=E2=80=99t listen to it now. Imagine a tiger and a lion=
 talking.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Crypto and celebrity were an odd symbiosis: A =
lot of crypto projects were valued mainly on=C2=A0<em>attention</em>; the t=
hing that makes, say, Dogecoin valuable is that a lot of people wanted to t=
rade Dogecoin, not any underlying fundamentals. So paying directly for atte=
ntion =E2=80=94 hiring Tom Brady to just put his face next to an ad saying =
=E2=80=9Chere have some crypto=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0was a sensible move =
for crypto firms. =E2=80=9CFor a while crypto was probably the highest bidd=
er for celebrity and influence,=E2=80=9D I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/32004867.263405/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS=
9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMjYvZnR4LXNwZW50LWJpZy1vbi1jZWxlYnJpdHk_Y=
21waWQ9QkJEMDcwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5l=
d3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNzA2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cBce3ca804" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">wrote the other day</a>, about FTX=E2=80=
=99s celebrity operation.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Similarly, if you were a celebrity during the =
crypto boom, crypto technology seemed to offer a more lucrative and efficie=
nt way to turn celebrity into money than most previous methods. If you are =
Tom Brady you can autograph a football and sell it to someone but:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You gotta get the football, and a pen=
, and sign it, and ship it.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Not ev=
ery rich person who loves Tom Brady has a room where they display footballs=
, and even if they do, the number of people who come to the room is going t=
o be fairly small, putting some limit on the value of this trophy.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Whereas with non-fungible tokens:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You can sell someone, like, a digital=
 receipt conveying the information =E2=80=9Cyou bought this receipt from To=
m Brady,=E2=80=9D which has basically zero marginal cost to you. You can se=
ll an edition of 10,000 of them in five seconds.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;">The <em>buyers=E2=80=99</em>=C2=A0marginal cost of=C2=A0<em>=
displaying=C2=A0</em>that receipt is basically zero; it lives online, and t=
hey can broadcast to everyone on Twitter or whatever, =E2=80=9Clook, I got =
this Tom Brady NFT.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">For a=
 while a lot of crypto people had a lot of money and spent it on these thin=
gs; I cannot explain it; even from the vantage point of 2023 it seems so al=
ien.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That Times story also says:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2021, Mr. Brady also co-founded Autograph, =
which helps famous people sell the crypto collectibles known as nonfungible=
 tokens, or NFTs. Autograph raised more than $200 million from investors, a=
nd Mr. Bankman-Fried joined the board. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Brady=E2=80=99s other crypto venture has a=
lso struggled. Autograph=E2=80=99s revenue sank last year amid the crypto m=
eltdown, a person familiar with its finances said. The start-up has shifted=
 its strategy to focus more on helping celebrities find ways to foster loya=
lty with their fans, and less on marketing crypto tokens to consumers, the =
person said. The firm has also removed some crypto language from its market=
ing, downplaying terms like NFT, another person with knowledge of the compa=
ny said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For a split second =E2=80=9Chelp famous people=
 sell NFTs=E2=80=9D seemed like a big business. What a weird time 2021 was.=
</p>
